This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses data augmentation techniques for training deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of labeled data and benchmarking suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of state-of-the-art methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
